OL,5,Ckilled'
OL,7,FAlan Wilson, senior coroner, opened
OL,8,Fthe three-day inquest into Ms Leitch's
OL,9,Fdeath on Monday, 14 October, and
OL,10,Frevealed Clarke had refused to take
OL,11,Fpart in the process.
OL,13,FHe described the case as "particularly
OL,14,Fsad" and "tragic", listing failings on
OL,15,Fthe part of the professionals who
OL,16,Fvisited Debbie's home before she died.
OL,18,FMr Wilson said the family GP did not
OL,19,Fshow enough professional curiosity
OL,20,Fwhen they visited, despite Debbie's
OL,21,Fweight loss and incontinence.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
