OL,7,F"We know Deborah's mother manipulated
OL,8,Fcircumstances through disguised
OL,9,Fcompliance when dealing with
OL,10,Fprofessionals so that her neglect was
OL,11,Fnot apparent to ourselves and other
OL,12,Fagencies visiting their home and that
OL,13,Fshe was subsequently convicted of
OL,14,Fgross negligence manslaughter in 2022.
OL,16,F"However, it is clear from the work
OL,17,Fundertaken since the time of Deborah's
OL,18,Fdeath in 2019 and the review that was
OL,19,Fpublished in 2023 that there were
OL,20,Fmissed opportunities and Deborah's
OL,21,Fvoice was seldom heard.
OL,26,@oD@AOUxD@AOU
